objects.name: Windy Phoenix
objects.description:
Windy Phoenix, also known as Windshift, is a threat actor group that mainly pursue Middle Easter goverment targets. Initially debuted by DarkMatter. 

This group instead of attacking enterprise as a whole they target individuals, with years of recon and trust building relationship.

objects.name: Campaign 1 - Windy Phoenix
objects.description: In August of 2018, DarkMatter released a report entitled “In the Trails of Windy Phoenix APT”, which unveiled a threat actor with TTPs very similar to those of Bahamut. Subsequently, two additional articles (here and here) were released by Objective-See which provide an analysis of some validated Windy Phoenix samples targeting OSX systems. Pivoting on specific file attributes and infrastructure indicators, Unit 42 was able to identify and correlate additional attacker activity and can now provide specific details on a targeted Windy Phoenix attack as it unfolded at a Middle Eastern government agency.
